// DGR INFOHAS Expansion — based on the 40-page Academy INFOHAS Dangerous Goods
// Awareness Manual (16-hour cabin crew course, 11 chapters).
//
// This file adds DEEP, DETAILED content (500+ words per lesson) for DGR lessons
// mapped to the Academy INFOHAS DG Awareness training manual chapters. Content
// is merged with the base lesson content at runtime.
//
// CHAPTER MAP (Academy INFOHAS DG Awareness Manual):
//   Ch1  — Introduction to Dangerous Goods (definitions, why regulated, hidden DG, crew role)
//   Ch2  — ICAO & IATA Regulations (Annex 18, Doc 9284, DGR hierarchy, passenger info)
//   Ch3  — Responsibilities of Cabin Crew (pre-flight, boarding, in-flight, post-incident, crew matrix)
//   Ch4  — Nine Hazard Classes (definitions, examples, hazards, passenger relevance)
//   Ch5  — Hazard Labels & Markings (label anatomy, handling labels, CAO zero tolerance)
//   Ch6  — Passenger Dangerous Goods (allowance table, hidden DG vigilance, decision tree)
//   Ch7  — Lithium Batteries (chemistry, thermal runaway 5 stages, Wh ratings, recognition signs)
//   Ch8  — Electronic Devices & PEDs (e-cigarettes, smart baggage, mobility aids, medical equipment)
//   Ch9  — DG Emergencies (types, cabin emergency equipment, PBE)
//   Ch10 — SFF Procedure (6 steps: detect-alert-protect-attack-contain-document, NITS format)
//   Ch11 — Case Studies (lithium fire in overhead bin, e-cig in checked bag, cabin smoke)
//
// Plus: 10 MCQ assessment, 5 short answer, 3 practical exercises, glossary (25 terms), references.

